Download and Install Virtual Box from the following link:
http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/server-storage/virtualbox/downloads/index.html

Download ISO file of Ubuntu Server from the following link:
http://www.ubuntu.com/download/server

Environment Details:
Host Operating System: Windows 8.1
Virtual Box: Version 4.3.26 r98988

Click New and enter the details as below
New
	Name: 		Ubuntu Linux 14.04.2 LTS
	Type:		Linux
	Version:	Ubuntu (64 bit)

Memory Size
Default is 512 MB. You can increase the size to 1024 MB or 2048 MB as per your RAM availability.

Hard Drive
	Select the option “Create a virtual hard drive now”.

Hard drive file type
	VDI (VirtualBox Disk Image)

Storage on physical hard drive
	Dynamically allocated

File Location and Size
	If you want you can change the disk size from the default 8 GB to as per your needs.

Click on Create.

Your newly created virtual machine “Ubuntu Linux 14.04.2 LTS” appears on the list of virtual machines on the left panel.
